Trees are one of the most important data structures in DSA. Almost every big company asks tree questions because they test recursion, DFS, BFS, problem-solving, and algorithmic thinking.

A Tree is a non-linear hierarchical data structure made up of nodes connected by edges.

Example:

        1
       / \
      2   3
     / \
    4   5
1 is connected to 2 and 3.
2 is connected to 4 and 5.

Unlike arrays or linked lists, trees branch into multiple paths.


